folder: Cumberland Street & Park Avenue, Brooklyn, NY
text:
Cumberland Street, east side, south from (No. 101) a point midway between Park and Myrtle Avenues, looking toward the latter. The auto parking space is the former site of the Brooklyn Cancer Institute. View 2 is south across the Myrtle Avenue elevated trestle. These buildings were later demolished and the site made part of Fort Greene Houses, a low-rent city housing center.

October 10, 1940
Views 1,2

P. L. Sperr

folder: Park Avenue & Cumberland Street, Brooklyn, NY
text:
Park Avenue, north side, east from Cumberland Street to Carlton Avenue. The buildings beyond Carlton Avenue are obstructed from view by the truck. View 2 shows some of the houses as seen from Carlton Avenue, looking west.

P. L. Sperr
October 10, 1940
Views 1,2
View 3: April 11, 1941

View 3 shows the same block of houses, i.e., the north side of Park Avenue between Carlton Avenue (right) and Cumberland Street. The buildings on the south side of the avenue were demolished for the erection of Park Green Houses.
